                            <comment id="28416" author="skaffman" created="Sun, 9 Dec 2007 20:34:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that RuntimeExceptions are propagated OK, so perhaps this is only a problem when logging checked exceptions?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="28460" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2007 04:38:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, we should simply propagate checked exceptions as-is there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="29034" author="hanswesterbeek" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2008 19:04:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi juergen,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I believe the behaviour described above still persists in portlet-mvc version 2.5.1&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe the fix still needs to be propagated to DispatcherPortlet?&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;regards,&lt;br/&gt;
hans&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="29102" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 17 Jan 2008 00:07:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Indeed, it appears we missed some reflective invocations for Spring 2.5.1 there... I&apos;ve fixed those for Spring 2.5.2 - should be available in the next nightly 2.5.2 snapshot (to be available from &lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springframework.org/downloads/nightly/snapshot-download.php?project=SPR&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springframework.org/downloads/nightly/snapshot-download.php?project=SPR&lt;/a&gt;)!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
